<section class="problem-section">
  <div class="problem-inner">

    <div class="problem-image">
      <img
        src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/AppaaThe/Rituel-store/main/product-images/rituel-problem.jpg"
        alt="Woman looking tired at her reflection in the morning"
        loading="lazy"
      >
    </div>

    <div class="problem-copy">
      <span class="section-label">Sound Familiar?</span>

      <h2 class="problem-title">You wake up looking<br><em>more tired than you feel.</em></h2>

      <div class="problem-list">
        <div class="problem-item">
          <span class="problem-dash">—</span>
          <p>Your face is puffy. Every morning. No matter how much water you drank or how early you went to bed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <span class="problem-dash">—</span>
          <p>Your jawline has softened. You see it in photos. You don't say anything but you notice.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <span class="problem-dash">—</span>
          <p>You've spent money on serums, creams, eye patches. Your skin still looks the same at 7am.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="problem-item">
          <span class="problem-dash">—</span>
          <p>You want to look like yourself — just the best version. Without a full makeup routine before 8am.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="problem-pivot">
        The problem isn't your skin. It's that no cream can physically move fluid, drain puffiness, or lift your facial muscles. Only mechanical stimulation can do that. That's what gua sha is.
      </p>

      <a href="#shop" class="btn-problem">Start the Ritual</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

